<figureCitation box="[1038,1053,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="6.[144,223,1156,1175]" captionTargetBox="[399,1167,196,1126]" captionTargetId="figure-319@6.[399,1167,196,1126]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 5. Leptoptilos robustus sp. nov., distal part of left ulna (LBA-XI-02). A, ventral view; B, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cdu, condylus dorsalis ulnae; cvu, condylus ventralis ulnae; dr, depression radialis; f, foramen; itc, incisura tuberculi carpalis; pr, papillae remigales; si, sulcus intercondylaris; tc, tuberculum carpale. Scale bar = 50 mm. Photographs by E. Kruidenier." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757505/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="714">5</figureCitation>
