<figureCitation box="[1099,1114,1759,1781]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="10.[144,223,1273,1292]" captionTargetBox="[399,1167,195,1243]" captionTargetId="figure-235@10.[399,1167,195,1243]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 9. Leptoptilos robustus sp. nov., distal left tibiotarsus (LBA-XI-04). A, anterior view of specimen; B, anterior view of distal fragment; C, posterior view of distal fragment. Abbreviations: cs, location of natural fracture at which cross-section is visible; dce, distal opening of canalis extensorius; fcd, facies caudalis; fcr, facies cranialis; gm, gnawing marks; pce, proximal opening of canalis extensorius; pst, pons supratendineus; se, sulcus extensorius; tub, tubercle laterodistal of the pons supratendineus. Scale bars = 50 mm. Photographs by E. Kruidenier." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757513/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="714">9</figureCitation>
