<paragraph blockId="8.[144,758,1610,1693]" pageId="8" pageNumber="715">
<emphasis box="[144,269,1610,1631]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="715">Etymology:</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meijer &amp; Due" authorityYear="2010" box="[462,560,1610,1631]" class="Aves" family="Ciconiidae" genus="Leptoptilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ciconiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="715" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[462,560,1610,1631]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="715">robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning ‘strong, robust’, and referring to the large tibiotarsus and the thickness of its cortex.
</paragraph>
