<figureCitation box="[1012,1077,1495,1517]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[144,223,1380,1399]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,198,1347]" captionTargetId="figure-223@2.[144,1424,196,1350]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Stratigraphical sequence of the Sector VII/XI trench. Remains from Leptoptilos robustus sp. nov. were retrieved from Sector XI, spits 43–47, which correspond to Layers O–P. The white tuffaceous layer is indicated by Na-d and has been dated at 11–17 kya. From Morwood et al. (2005), reprinted with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757499/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="715">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
